Ok, I've got two different copies of the Qwen Code repo that I'm working on.  In ./qwen-local is a version that I've modified extensively - to the point that I broke it.  The modifications were aimed at converting Qwen Code to being fully local, using LM Studio as the default backend LLM server.  I implemented several userful new commands, but then I tinkered too much with the core logic and broke it beyond repair.  So I started a new repo with a fresh copy that I'm calling LowCal coder, it's located in ./LowCal.  What I want you to do is extract some of the good features from ./qwen-local and implement them into ./LowCal.  The first one is the /model command - it uses LM Studio's /v1/ endpoint to fetch all available models and lets the user switch between models at will.  It also unloads the current model before loading the new one, and always displays the currently loaded model in the status bar (even if the user changes it within LM Studio itself, without using the /model command).  In ./qwen-local, you can read QWEN.md, GEMINI.md, AGENTS.md, and README.md for comprehensive overviews of the package, as well as any other files you need to accomplish the task.  Let's go!
